Duke Energy has investments in various joint ventures with pipeline projects currently under construction. These entities are considered VIEs due to
having insufficient equity to finance their own activities without subordinated financial support. Duke Energy does not have the power to direct the
activities that most significantly impact the economic performance, the obligation to absorb losses or the right to receive benefits of these VIEs and
therefore does not consolidate these entities.
